@startuml PaymentFlow_Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

title Data Flow: Payment Processing (State Pattern)

actor User
participant "Browser" as Browser #E1F5FE
participant "BookingController" as Controller #FFF3E0
participant "Booking Entity" as Booking #FCE4EC
participant "BookingState\n(implementation)" as State #FFC97C
participant "Payment Entity" as PaymentE #FCE4EC
participant "BookingRepository" as Repo #E8F5E9
participant "Database" as DB #EEEEEE
participant "EmailNotificationListener" as Listener #F3E5F5

User -> Browser: Click "Pay"\nEnter amount\nClick "Submit Payment"

Browser -> Controller: POST /bookings/{id}/pay\n?amount=500

Controller -> Repo: findById(bookingId)
Repo -> DB: SELECT * FROM BOOKING WHERE id = ?
DB --> Repo: return Booking entity
Repo --> Controller: return Booking

note right of Repo
    @PostLoad annotation triggers
    booking.init() method:
    • Deserialize status_string
    • Set current_status object
    • If status="PARTIALLY_PAID"
      → PartiallyPaidState()
end note

Controller -> Booking: pay(amount = 500.0)

Booking -> Booking: Create Payment object\nnewPayment.setAmount(500)\nnewPayment.setPaymentDate(today)

Booking -> Booking: payments.add(newPayment)

Booking -> Booking: if (current_status == null)\n  current_status = WaitingForPaymentState

Booking -> State: current_status.pay(this, 500.0)

alt Check State Type
  alt If WaitingForPaymentState
    State -> State: amountRemaining = total_price - 500\nif (amountRemaining <= 0)\n  → setStatus(PaidState)\nelse\n  → setStatus(PartiallyPaidState)
  else If PartiallyPaidState
    State -> State: totalPaid = getAmountPaid() + 500\namountRemaining = total_price - totalPaid\nif (amountRemaining <= 0)\n  → setStatus(PaidState)\nelse\n  → stay in PartiallyPaidState
  else If PaidState
    State -> State: Already paid, stay PaidState\n(or handle extra payment)
  else If CancelledState
    State -> State: Cannot pay cancelled booking
  end
end

State --> Booking: State updated\nstatus_string synchronized

note right of State
    STATE PATTERN
    Each state knows what to do
    with a payment

    @PreUpdate annotation will
    trigger syncStatus():
    • current_status → status_string
    • status_string = "PARTIALLY_PAID"
      or "PAID"
end note

Booking -> Repo: save(booking)\n@PreUpdate syncStatus()

Repo -> DB: UPDATE BOOKING SET\nstatus = 'PARTIALLY_PAID',\ntotal_paid = 500\nWHERE id = ?

Repo -> DB: INSERT INTO PAYMENT\n(booking_id, amount, payment_date)

DB --> Repo: OK

Repo --> Controller: return updated Booking

Controller -> Listener: Publish BookingStatusChangedEvent\n(booking, newStatus)

Listener -> Listener: Receive event\nPrepare email notification

note right of Listener
    EVENT/LISTENER PATTERN
    Observer pattern for notifications
    • Decoupled from main flow
    • Can send email, SMS, etc.
    • Async processing possible
end note

Controller -> Browser: return updated HTML fragment\nShow:\n• New status "PARTIALLY_PAID"\n• Amount paid: 500\n• Amount remaining: 500

Browser -> User: Display:\n✓ Payment accepted\n• Status changed\n• Show payment history

par Async Operations
  Listener -> Listener: Send email notification\n"Payment received for booking #123"
end

note right of PaymentE
    PAYMENT ENTITY
    • booking_id (FK)
    • amount
    • payment_date
    • Created by Booking.pay()
    • CascadeType.ALL ensures
      payments are deleted when
      booking is deleted
end note

@enduml

